# R6 Class Representing DataMatricesBVARPANEL

The class DataMatricesBVARPANEL presents the data matrices of dependent
variables, \\\mathbf{Y}\_c\\, and regressors, \\\mathbf{X}\_c\\, for the
Bayesian Panel VAR model for all countries \\c = 1, ..., C\\.

## Public fields

- `Y`:

  a list with `C` elements with `(T_c + p) x N` matrices of dependent
  variables, \\\mathbf{Y}\_c\\, possibly with missing observations given
  by `NA`.

- `missing`:

  a list with `C` elements with `T_c x N` matrices containing value `1`
  for missing observation and `0` otherwise.

- `type`:

  an `N` character vector with elements set to "rate" or "real"
  determining the truncation of the predictive density to `[0, 100]` and
  `(-Inf, Inf)` (no truncation) for each of the variables.

- `exogenous`:

  a list with `C` elements with `(T_c + p) x N` matrices of exogenous
  variables.

### Method `new()`

Create new data matrices DataMatricesBVARPANEL

#### Usage

    specify_panel_data_matrices$new(
      data,
      p = 1L,
      exogenous = NULL,
      type = rep("real", ncol(data[[1]]))
    )

#### Arguments

- `data`:

  a list containing `(T_c+p)xN` matrices with country-specific time
  series data.

- `p`:

  a positive integer providing model's autoregressive lag order.

- `exogenous`:

  a list containing `(T_c+p)xd` matrices with country-specific of
  exogenous variables. This matrix should not include a constant term.

- `type`:

  an `N` character vector with elements set to "rate" or "real"
  determining the truncation of the predictive density to `[0, 100]` and
  `(-Inf, Inf)` (no truncation) for each of the variables.
